name: pfpicardi
tweet: For any Warren supporter who‚Äôs looking for a new home and would like to chat, my DMs are open. No matter what, it was in the spirit of her campaign that we will all vote to get Donald Trump out of the White House come November. Now we must, as @AOC said, #buildtogether.

name: pfpicardi
tweet: This race is not over. This fight is not over. And I believe we can sway opinion, change policies, and bring change to the White House by buckling down and fighting, arm in arm. We are better together. #NotMeUs

name: pfpicardi
tweet: At the same time, I encourage the Sanders supporters who hear those critiques to not brush them aside dismissively, but to reach out to folks one-on-one to let them know that this spirit is not what the campaign is about or represents.

name: pfpicardi
tweet: If we are truly better than this toxicity, we should work to change that perception‚Äîby listening to the progressive women who support Sanders more intently than we do the trolls. I personally will be doing so by engaging in conversations about this matter OFF Twitter.

name: pfpicardi
tweet: It is a fact that women make up a significant base of Sanders‚Äô supporters, and many of those are women I respect greatly. I have listened to them when they said they feel erased by this narrative‚Äîby a toxic minority of men who shout loudly on Twitter.

name: pfpicardi
tweet: I know many Warren supporters are still licking their wounds. I have many friends who say they are wary of supporting Sanders because of the culture surrounding his campaign. I admit that I have also felt that, but I want to add something here.

name: pfpicardi
tweet: That‚Äôs why I am voting for Senator @BernieSanders in the New York primary, and why I hope you will, too. A primary is the place to vote our values‚Äîand on immigration, corruption, healthcare, and criminal justice‚Äîhe represents the best of those forward-thinking values.

name: pfpicardi
tweet: Anyone who insists that we must ‚Äúfall in line‚Äù one way or another is betraying our democratic process. This is still a primary! Sanders is still in this race! Primaries, regardless of who wins them, can help shape the electorate and the one who will eventually be elected!

name: pfpicardi
tweet: It would be disingenuous to say that I supported Warren for her policies and now choose to support anyone but Sanders. It is a fact that most of her policies ideologically align with those of @BernieSanders, and that he's been a champion of these ideals in American politics.

name: pfpicardi
tweet: But the results of Super Tuesday showed me that we need to align behind the candidate best suited for what will bring our country forward. @BernieSanders built a progressive coalition‚Äîa surge of American voters who are hoping for change in politics.

name: pfpicardi
tweet: But every vote is a vote earned, not a vote owed. I reject the notion that she didn‚Äôt earn the right to see this race through to Super Tuesday. I also reject the notion that she has interrupted Sanders‚Äô momentum‚Äîand the numbers show that. Warren deserved to fight.

name: pfpicardi
tweet: I, along with many of her other supporters, was dismayed at the #SuperTuesday results. I am sad to see that, even as she captivated audiences and the American public (and helped blockade Bloomberg from buying this election), voters did not turn out to support her.

name: pfpicardi
tweet: I decided to endorse Elizabeth Warren because I believed she was not getting a fair shake, and that‚Äîlike so many other women who dare to take the stage in American politics‚Äîshe was being held to a higher standard, and was asked to play by a different set of rules.

name: pfpicardi
tweet: First, I have to say that Elizabeth Warren has always been my first choice. I was drawn to her blend of progressive policy and pragmatism, and felt she was the best-prepared and most impactful at the debates, especially in articulating her ideas.

name: pfpicardi
tweet: I was so encouraged by the campaign @ewarren ran: one of unity, positivity, and progressive policy met with a legislator‚Äôs pragmatism. I‚Äôm working with her team, it never felt like politics. This felt from the heart. I hope we all take these elements of her candidacy forward.
